---
import SectionMarker from "./SectionMarker.astro";
---
<section class="section snowflake" data-section-num="05" id="s05" aria-labelledby="stor-headline">
  <SectionMarker num="05" label="The shift" right="Before / after" />
  <p class="label">The shift</p>
  <h2 id="stor-headline">From snowflake chaos to a standard runtime.</h2>
  <div class="two-col">
    <div>
      <h3>Before</h3>
      <p>
        Your first Cursor-built <strong>ticketing tool</strong> took a weekend. The fourth —
        a <strong>customer-ops console</strong> — has a migration your team lead refuses to run.
      </p>
      <p>
        The <strong>back-office dashboard</strong> you built last month passes tests, but fires two
        events on every retry. You spent more time reviewing AI diffs than writing anything new.
      </p>
      <p class="stor-muted"><em>The agent didn't slow down. Your architecture did.</em></p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3>After</h3>
      <p>
        A week from now, service #5 is a blueprint you edited in 40 minutes. The runtime is the
        same one #1 runs. The diff is 12 lines of JSON.
      </p>
      <p>
        Your team lead signs off in five minutes — the runtime didn't change, only the domain.
        You tell the agent "build an escalation flow" and it writes a blueprint, not a repo.
      </p>
      <p class="stor-shift"><span>Shift →</span></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .snowflake .two-col > div > h3 { margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
  .stor-muted { color: var(--color-text-muted); }
  .stor-shift {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-small);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-label);
    color: var(--color-accent-text);
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
